{{Infobox language |name=Millcayac |states=[[Argentina]], dispossessed to [[Chile]] |ethnicity= [[Huarpe people]] |extinct=few Huarpean speakers left by 1630 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Huarpean languages|Huarpean]] |iso3=none |linglist=qgb|lingname=(Milykayak) |glotto=mill1237 |glottorefname=Millcayac }}
'''Millcayac''' (Milykayak) was one of two known [[Warpean languages]]. It was native to [[Cuyo Province|Cuyo]] in Argentina, but was displaced to Chile in the late 16th century. [[Luis de Valdivia]] wrote a grammar, vocabulary and religious texts. The people became mestizo and lost their language soon after.
